<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
The known male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kang &amp; Whitfield &amp; Owens &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Mercado" baseAuthorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Neocardiochiles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neocardiochiles whitfieldi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whitfieldi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Neocardiochiles whitfieldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from other members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Neocardiochiles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neocardiochiles" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Neocardiochiles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following color characters: head and mesosoma darker; wings entirely melanic; metasoma orange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
